| Bill Would Require Labels on Cloned Food                           |
|   from the it-tastes-exactly-the-same dept.                        |
|   posted by samzenpus on Wednesday April 18, @20:20 (Biotech)      |
|   http://science.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/04/18/2234217      |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

ComeBack writes "Steaks, pork chops, milk and other products from cloned
livestock would have to be [0]clearly labeled on grocers' shelves under a
bill pending in the California Legislature. If passed, the requirement
could be more stringent than federal rules. The Food and Drug
Administration is poised to give final approval to meat and milk from
cloned animals [1]without any special labeling, though a bill introduced
in Congress would require it."

