| The World's Longest Tunnel                                         |
|   from the disaster-movie-soon-to-follow dept.                     |
|   posted by samzenpus on Wednesday April 18, @21:25 (United States)|
|   http://slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/04/18/2240257              |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]fusconed writes "Bloomberg reports that the Russian government is
proposing to build an underground [1]tunnel between Russia and Alaska for
transporting goods, electricity and natural resources. The tunnel would
be twice as long as that between the UK and France. The $10 — $12b cost
is not something to be overlooked, but Russia claims the benefits would
pay it off in 20 years. It would take 10 to 15 years to build, but being
an Alaskan, it sounds good to me!"

